      "writtenOn": "2020-04-09T01:46:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "No. LitElement is just a bridge between typeof this and T.\n\nProvider has to be T. and T has to extend LitElement. This is defined in L104.\nIn L107, we casted cls from Constructor\u003cT\u003e to Constructor\u003cLitElement\u003e, (due to some typescript limitation) we lost the information.\n\ninheritance graph from tsc\u0027s point of view:\nLitElement -\u003e Provider\nLitElement -\u003e T\nT is a sibling class of Provider.\n\ninheritance graph from our point of view:\nLitElement -\u003e T -\u003e Provider\n\nSo we ended up with type mismatch issue. In order to cast an instance from Provider to T, we need to upcast to a common parent class, which is LitElement in this case.",
      "parentUuid": "c2f043be_cf39393e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 160,
