      "message": "I think my drive towards a stricter (often more complex) type system comes from my frustration of dealing with weaker type systems, where I need to keep track of a lot of constraints/invariants because they are not encoded in the type system.\nWith a stricter type system, although it\u0027s harder to make the complier happy or to understand the type interface initially, (IMO) it\u0027s easier to code later on because I no longer need to keep track of the constraints since the type system can do most of the work.\nBut I don\u0027t have enough experience with large projects. Maybe the trade off is not justified.\n\n\u003e \u003e the interfaces they expose are actually quite simple\n\u003e I think it is bold claim. As a user of this func, I have to read\nThat\u0027s poorly worded. I agree that the type is quite hard to comprehend. I meant the usage of lib should be quite simple. Most notably, there\u0027s very little thing to manually keep track of once you get it working.",
